-- U.K. Reassures Banks, Companies Over Falklands, Telegraph Says
-- B y   B e n   M o s h i n s k y
-- 2012-04-22T10:37:18Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-22/u-k-reassures-companies-over-falklands-sunday-telegraph-says.html
The U.K. government has written to
15 banks and oil companies operating in the Falkland Islands to
reassure them in the wake of legal threats made by  Argentina ,
the Sunday Telegraph  reported , citing a Foreign Office letter.  The companies are entitled to develop oil and fishing
industries around the disputed islands without interference from
Argentina, the letter said, according to the report.  The Foreign Office confirmed a letter had been sent in
March.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ben Moshinsky in London at 
